The paper discusses a case study in Horn clause verification for sorting programs. Horn clauses are commonly used in logic and theorem proving, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of functional programming, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL). The focus on verification and elimination of inductive data structures suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Data Structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper specifically discusses sorting algorithms, which falls under Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
